    	<h4>Right triangle altitude theorem</h4>
		h : altitude (or height) on the hypotenuse<br>
		p : projection of leg a on the hypotenuse<br>
		q : projection of leg b on the hypotenuse<br>
		<br>
		The square of the altitude on the hypotenuse is equal to the geometric me=
an of the projections of the legs (non-hypotenuse sides) on the hypotenuse.=
